11.body: Kit is a raccoon. He is interested in astronomy, amateur radio and video editing. Kit is an andromorph but his preference towards modest clothing makes this naturally discrete. Kit believes in truth and justice along with a code of conduct. This often gets him involved in investigative journalism. He occasionally winds up at odds with the police who sometimes question his interpretations of the law. The majority of his interpretations are correct but the rare instances he messes up usually wind up getting him trouble with the very laws he tries to help enforce. Kit sometimes used as a scapegoat for the police and politicians when those situations occur.
11.title: Kit Welsh

13.body: Felix is a Hudson android owned by Savelli Cornell . His natural curiosity means his interests are often derive on what Savelli himself interested in. Due to his programming, Felix naturally seeks to be friendly and generous towards those around him. Savelli's mischievous behavior often puts him at odds with what he was designed to do that he is often finds himself doing what is right, in spite of Savelli's orders. This occasionally puts him in direct contact with Kit Welsh .
13.title: Felix Cornell

15.body: Oliver is a blue tabby cat that is interested in cars, soccer, and coin collecting.
15.title: Oliver Bradford

17.body: Savelli is a Dalmatian that is interested in martial arts, hacking and VR gaming. He owns an Hudson android named Felix . Savelli often chooses to exploit loopholes established within system in order to achieve his goals. These goals range from pure selfishness to just making life better for himself. Savelli has a "Honor Among Thieves" mentality but he himself will not promise anything unless he knows he can truly keep them. Despite his questionable actions, he is genuinely a kind-hearted person. Savelli isn't necessarily a bad person but he isn't always good one ether.
17.title: Savelli Cornell

19.body: Max is a fennec with cybernetic eye and arm implants. He is interested in programming, photography and video games.
19.title: Max Hillward

2.body: Tailmaws are blind sentient tails with a mouth. They're able to eat and consume the same food as their host and get additional energy. Some tailmaws are capable of eating more than what their hosts are capable of.
2.title: Tailmaw

21.body: Zach Casey is a blue fox. He is interested in skateboarding, podcasting and comics. His first name is sometimes spelled Zack.
21.title: Zach Casey

23.body: Tom Wilcox is a border collie that is interested in model railroading, record collecting and karaoke. He is a andromorph .
23.title: Tom Wilcox

3.body: In Casey Universe, an andromorph is a fancy term for males born with female genitals. Andromorphs may share one or more sexual traits of their female counterparts.
3.title: Andromorph

6.body: Hudson are a brand of hospitality androids built out of various flexible alloys with synthetic fur and hair. They're normally designed to look like fennecs.
6.title: Hudson

7.body: Carter are a brand of combat androids built similar to the Hudson models but lack fur and hair. Carter androids normally designed to look like bulldogs.
7.title: Carter

9.body: Anthony is a blue fennec that is interested in electronics, model railroading and comics. He is a andromorph with a preference to more feminine bottoms. Anthony has a tailmaw named Fitz. Anthony believes in a healthy balance of freedom and doing good.
9.title: Anthony Foxclaw
